gi|6320064: DEFINITION:Arf family GTPase ARF2 [Saccharomyces cerevisiae S288C]

gi|6320009: DEFINITION:Arf family GTPase ARF1 [Saccharomyces cerevisiae S288C]

gi|6324668: DEFINITION:Arf family GTPase ARF3 [Saccharomyces cerevisiae S288C]

gi|6319641: DEFINITION:Arf family GTPase ARL1 [Saccharomyces cerevisiae S288C]

gi|6323787: DEFINITION:Arf family GTPase CIN4 [Saccharomyces cerevisiae S288C]

note:GTP-binding protein involved in beta-tubulin (Tub2p) folding; isolated as mutant with increased chromosome loss and sensitivity to benomyl; regulated by the GTPase-activating protein, Cin2p, the human retinitis pigmentosa 2 (RP2) homolog
gi|6325206: DEFINITION:Arf family GTPase ARL3 [Saccharomyces cerevisiae S288C]

gi|6325038: Vesicle coat complex COPII, GTPase subunit SAR1

gi|14318517: GTP-binding protein SEC4, small G protein superfamily, and related Ras family GTP-binding proteins
DEFINITION:Rab family GTPase SEC4 [Saccharomyces cerevisiae S288C]

note:Rab family GTPase; essential for vesicle-mediated exocytic secretion and autophagy; associates with the exocyst component Sec15p and may regulate polarized delivery of transport vesicles to the exocyst at the plasma membrane; exocyst association is negatively regulated via phosphorylation by Cdc5p during cytokinesis
gi|6320858: G-protein alpha subunit (small G protein superfamily)
DEFINITION:guanine nucleotide-binding protein subunit alpha [Saccharomyces cerevisiae S288C]

note:Nucleotide binding alpha subunit of the heterotrimeric G protein; interacts with the receptor Gpr1p, has signaling role in response to nutrients; required for the recruitment of Ras-GTP at the plasma membrane and in the nucleus
gi|6321792: G-protein alpha subunit (small G protein superfamily)
DEFINITION:guanine nucleotide-binding protein subunit alpha [Saccharomyces cerevisiae S288C]

note:Subunit of G protein involved in pheromone response; GTP-binding alpha subunit of heterotrimeric G protein; negatively regulates mating pathway by sequestering G(beta)gamma and triggering an adaptive response; activates Vps34p at endosome; protein abundance increases in response to DNA replication stress; mutations in human homolog GNAS associated with McCune-Albright syndrome
gi|14318480: GTPase Rab1/YPT1, small G protein superfamily, and related GTP-binding proteins
DEFINITION:Rab family GTPase YPT1 [Saccharomyces cerevisiae S288C]

gi|6320869: GTPase Rab11/YPT3, small G protein superfamily

gi|6321228: GTPase Rab11/YPT3, small G protein superfamily
DEFINITION:Rab family GTPase YPT32 [Saccharomyces cerevisiae S288C]

note:Rab family GTPase involved in the exocytic pathway; mediates intra-Golgi traffic or the budding of post-Golgi vesicles from the trans-Golgi; protein abundance increases in response to DNA replication stress; YPT32 has a paralog, YPT31, that arose from the whole genome duplication
gi|6324025: GTPase Rab11/YPT3, small G protein superfamily
DEFINITION:Rab family GTPase YPT11 [Saccharomyces cerevisiae S288C]

note:Rab GTPase; Myo2p-binding protein implicated in mother-to-bud transport of cortical endoplasmic reticulum (ER), late Golgi, and mitochondria during cell division; function is regulated at multiple levels; abundance of active Ypt11p forms is controlled by phosphorylation status and degradation; normally a low-abundance protein whose ER localization is only detected when protein is highly over expressed
gi|6322933: note:NAD-dependent 5,10-methylenetetrahydrafolate dehydrogenase; plays a catalytic role in oxidation of cytoplasmic one-carbon units; expression is regulated by Bas1p and Bas2p, repressed by adenine, and may be induced by inositol and choline
gi|6322695: Signal recognition particle receptor, beta subunit (small G protein superfamily)
DEFINITION:Signal recognition particle receptor subunit beta [Saccharomyces cerevisiae S288C]

gi|6322866: GTPase Rab5/YPT51 and related small G protein superfamily GTPases
DEFINITION:Rab family GTPase YPT52 [Saccharomyces cerevisiae S288C]

gi|6324236: GTPase Rab5/YPT51 and related small G protein superfamily GTPases
DEFINITION:Rab family GTPase YPT53 [Saccharomyces cerevisiae S288C]

gi|6324663: GTPase Rab5/YPT51 and related small G protein superfamily GTPases
DEFINITION:Rab family GTPase VPS21 [Saccharomyces cerevisiae S288C]

note:Endosomal Rab family GTPase; required for endocytic transport and sorting of vacuolar hydrolases; required for endosomal localization of the CORVET complex; required with YPT52 for MVB biogenesis and sorting; involved in autophagy and ionic stress tolerance; geranylgeranylation required for membrane association; protein abundance increases in response to DNA replication stress; mammalian Rab5 homolog; VPS21 has a paralog, YPT53, that arose from the whole genome duplication
gi|6321811: GTPase Rab3, small G protein superfamily
note:hypothetical protein; YHR022C is not an essential gene
gi|6323291: GTPase Rab6/YPT6/Ryh1, small G protein superfamily
DEFINITION:Rab family GTPase YPT6 [Saccharomyces cerevisiae S288C]

note:Rab family GTPase; required for endosome-to-Golgi, intra-Golgi retrograde, and retrograde Golgi-to-ER transport; temporarily at the Golgi, dissociating into the cytosol on arrival of the late Golgi GTPase Ypt32p; Golgi-localized form is GTP bound, while cytosolic form is GDP-bound; required for delivery of Atg9p to the phagophore assembly site during autophagy under heat stress, with Ypt6p for starvation induced autophagy and for the CVT pathway; homolog of mammalian Rab6
gi|6323324: GTPase Ran/TC4/GSP1 (nuclear protein transport pathway), small G protein superfamily

gi|6322426: DEFINITION:Hsp70 family ATPase KAR2 [Saccharomyces cerevisiae S288C]

note:ATPase involved in protein import into the ER; also acts as a chaperone to mediate protein folding in the ER and may play a role in ER export of soluble proteins; regulates the unfolded protein response via interaction with Ire1p
gi|6319314: DEFINITION:Hsp70 family ATPase SSA1 [Saccharomyces cerevisiae S288C]

note:ATPase involved in protein folding and NLS-directed nuclear transport; HSP70 family member; required for ubiquitin-dependent degradation of short-lived proteins; forms a chaperone complex with Ydj1p; localizes to the nucleus, cytoplasm and cell wall; unique functional specificity in the propagation of yeast [URE3] prions and vacuolar-mediated degradation of gluconeogenic enzymes; general targeting factor of Hsp104p to prion fibrils; 98% identity with paralog Ssa2p
gi|6319396: DEFINITION:Hsp70 family ATPase SSA3 [Saccharomyces cerevisiae S288C]

note:ATPase involved in protein folding and the response to stress; plays a role in SRP-dependent cotranslational protein-membrane targeting and translocation; member of the heat shock protein 70 (HSP70) family; localized to the cytoplasm; SSA3 has a paralog, SSA4, that arose from the whole genome duplication
gi|6319972: DEFINITION:Hsp70 family ATPase SSB1 [Saccharomyces cerevisiae S288C]

gi|6320950: DEFINITION:Hsp70 family chaperone SSA4 [Saccharomyces cerevisiae S288C]

note:Heat shock protein that is highly induced upon stress; plays a role in SRP-dependent cotranslational protein-membrane targeting and translocation; member of the HSP70 family; cytoplasmic protein that concentrates in nuclei upon starvation; SSA4 has a paralog, SSA3, that arose from the whole genome duplication
gi|6321855: note:Hsp70 protein that interacts with Zuo1p (a DnaJ homolog); interacts with Zuo1p to form a ribosome-associated complex that binds the ribosome via the Zuo1p subunit; also involved in pleiotropic drug resistance via sequential activation of PDR1 and PDR5; binds ATP
gi|6323004: DEFINITION:Hsp70 family chaperone SSA2 [Saccharomyces cerevisiae S288C]

gi|6324120: DEFINITION:Hsp70 family ATPase SSB2 [Saccharomyces cerevisiae S288C]

note:Cytoplasmic ATPase that is a ribosome-associated molecular chaperone; functions with J-protein partner Zuo1p; may be involved in the folding of newly-synthesized polypeptide chains; member of the HSP70 family; SSB2 has a paralog, SSB1, that arose from the whole genome duplication
gi|6320805: DEFINITION:Hsp70 family ATPase ECM10 [Saccharomyces cerevisiae S288C]

gi|6322505: DEFINITION:Hsp70 family ATPase SSC1 [Saccharomyces cerevisiae S288C]

gi|6323401: DEFINITION:Hsp70 family ATPase SSQ1 [Saccharomyces cerevisiae S288C]

gi|6319646: DEFINITION:adenyl-nucleotide exchange factor SSE2 [Saccharomyces cerevisiae S288C]

gi|6325151: DEFINITION:adenyl-nucleotide exchange factor SSE1 [Saccharomyces cerevisiae S288C]

note:ATPase component of heat shock protein Hsp90 chaperone complex; serves as nucleotide exchange factor to load ATP onto the SSA class of cytosolic Hsp70s; plays a role in prion propagation and determining prion variants; binds unfolded proteins; member of Hsp110 subclass of HSP70 proteins; deletion results in spindle elongation in S phase; SSE1 has a paralog, SSE2, that arose from the whole genome duplication
gi|6322777: DEFINITION:Hsp70 family chaperone LHS1 [Saccharomyces cerevisiae S288C]

gi|6319420: mRNA cleavage and polyadenylation factor I complex, subunit RNA15

gi|6321595: mRNA cleavage and polyadenylation factor I complex, subunit RNA15
DEFINITION:cleavage polyadenylation factor subunit PTI1 [Saccharomyces cerevisiae S288C]

gi|6321689: mRNA cleavage and polyadenylation factor I complex, subunit RNA15

gi|6325369: DEFINITION:RNA-binding ribosome biosynthesis protein MRD1 [Saccharomyces cerevisiae S288C]

gi|6319595: note:U1 snRNP A protein; homolog of human U1-A; involved in nuclear mRNA splicing
gi|6319689: note:RNA binding protein that negatively regulates growth rate; interacts with the 3' UTR of the mitochondrial porin (POR1) mRNA and enhances its degradation; overexpression impairs mitochondrial function; interacts with Dhh1p to mediate POR1 mRNA decay; expressed in stationary phase
gi|6319835: DEFINITION:single-stranded telomeric DNA-binding/mRNA-binding protein [Saccharomyces cerevisiae S288C]
